Sentencas: The present work is devoted to the comparative study of the absolute oxygen content, thermal expansion, electrical conductivity, and electrochemical performance of the La(1.6)Ln(0.4)NiO(4+delta) (Ln = La, Pr, Nd, Sm, Eu) complex oxides.
Titulo: Comprehensive study of functional properties and electrochemical performance of layered lanthanum nickelate substituted with rare-earth elements

Sentencas: The thermal expansion coefficients, obtained for the La(1.6)Ln(0.4)NiO(4+delta) compact samples, have approved thermomechanical compatibility of the materials with the Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 electrolyte.
Titulo: Comprehensive study of functional properties and electrochemical performance of layered lanthanum nickelate substituted with rare-earth elements

Sentencas: The highest conductivity value is found to be 107 S cm(-1) at 420 degrees C for the La1.6Sm0.4NiO4+delta sample.
Titulo: Comprehensive study of functional properties and electrochemical performance of layered lanthanum nickelate substituted with rare-earth elements

Sentencas: The results of scanning electron microscopy, performed after the cycle of measurements on two-layer electrodes with the La(1.6)Ln(0.4)NiO(4+delta) functional layers and the LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-delta (LNF) collector layers, have demonstrated the stability of the electrode structure under the measurement conditions and the maintenance of high average porosity for both layers.
Titulo: Comprehensive study of functional properties and electrochemical performance of layered lanthanum nickelate substituted with rare-earth elements

Sentencas: The minimum polarization resistance value, equal to 0.64 omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C, has been measured for the La1.6Eu0.4NiO4+delta electrode sintered at 1200 degrees C. Comprehensive distribution function of relaxation times (DFRT or DRT) analyses of the impedance data has been performed to establish the rate-limiting stages of the electrode reaction.
Titulo: Comprehensive study of functional properties and electrochemical performance of layered lanthanum nickelate substituted with rare-earth elements

Sentencas: Oxygen kinetic parameters calculated in the framework of the Adler-Lane-Steele (ALS) model with considering the microstructural parameters are shown to correlate well with those obtained from the isotope exchange data.
Titulo: Comprehensive study of functional properties and electrochemical performance of layered lanthanum nickelate substituted with rare-earth elements
